Previous Next McCook, Cozad golf teams qualify for state 
Kacee Samway, of McCook, watches a putt at Monument Shadows Golf Course in Gering on Monday. Samway qualified for the state tournament. (Jeff Fielder / World-Herald News Service) Posted: Monday, October 5, 2015 7:20 pm McCook, Cozad golf teams qualify for state Telegraph staff reports nptelegraph.com 
McCook finished second at the B-4 District meet at Monument Shadows Golf Course in Gering on Monday, qualifying for the state tournament. 
Hannah Kohl, of McCook, shot 83 to finish in third place behind Hannah Holloway, of Scottsbluff who shot 79, and Shelby Poynter, of Scottsbluff who shot 80.   Need an account? Create one now. Subscription required
